) 12nd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of Jamaica Avenue, showing an aaditbrium. One of the signs reads: "Meeting Rooas for Rent.' The wooded plot together with the auditorium was known as Columbia Park in 1909 and was, in all probability, a local picnic ground. It may have been C. Willow Street.
P. L. Sperr  Augost 22, 1932
